[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer-driven fuzzing run triggered a `FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium` exception [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating a Server Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m attempt. During processing of a ZIP[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive, code execution tried to open a network socket to “jazze.com:[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m” based on [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata derived from the untrusted input. The SSRF sanitizer detected and blocked the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexternal connection, flagging a potential security issue.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue type  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The report identifies a Server Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vulnerability. [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUntrusted data from a ZIP file entry was used to construct a network request, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleading to an attempted outbound connection.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- What happened  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. A fuzzing input triggered processing of a ZIP archive via Apache Commons [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCompress [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. While reading the central directory entries [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`readCentralDirectoryEntry` → [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`populateFromCentralDirectory`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the code invoked `[0m[1;35mURL.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` on an [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattacker-controlled URL.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Under the hood, `[0m[1;35mURL.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` created a socket [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mSocket.connect[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich was intercepted by Jazzer’s `ServerSideRequestForgery` sanitizer.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. The sanitizer raised [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium`, indicating an SSRF [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempt to “jazze.com:[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m”.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important observations  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The exception originates in the SSRF sanitizer [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`ServerSideRequestForgery.checkSsrf`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m rather than in application logic.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The network request path begins in `java.net.URL.openStream`, traversing [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstandard JDK classes [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`HttpClient`, `HttpURLConnection`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`CompressZipFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is the entry point [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand merely feeds input to the ZIP-processing library.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code areas for investigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The ZIP-processing logic in Apache Commons Compress, especially methods:  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – `ZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry`  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – `ZipFile.populateFromCentralDirectory`  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – All relevant constructors of `ZipFile` that accept untrusted streams or byte [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marrays  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Any application code that uses `[0m[1;35mURL.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or `[0m[1;35mSocket.connect[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` on data[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mderived from external inputs.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The integration points with Jazzer’s SSRF sanitizer [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`ServerSideRequestForgery.checkSsrf` and `checkSsrfSocket`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, to understand how [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muntrusted data reaches networking APIs.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`CompressZipFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to trace how input bytes flow into the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mZIP library and ultimately into `[0m[1;35mURL.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis issue highlights the need for careful handling of external references in [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive-processing code to prevent untrusted inputs from triggering outbound [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnetwork connections.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m192[0m[39m:        public Builder [0m[1;35msetMaxNumberOfDisks[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal long maxNumberOfDisks[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m193[0m[39m:            this.maxNumberOfDisks = maxNumberOfDisks;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m194[0m[39m:            return this;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m195[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m196[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m197[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m198[0m[39m:         * The actual channel, overrides any other input aspects like a File, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPath, and so on.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m199[0m[39m:         *[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m200[0m[39m:         * @param seekableByteChannel The actual channel.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m201[0m[39m:         * @return [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@code this[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m instance.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m202[0m[39m:         *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m203[0m[39m:        public Builder [0m[1;35msetSeekableByteChannel[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal SeekableByteChannel [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseekableByteChannel[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m204[0m[39m:            this.seekableByteChannel = seekableByteChannel;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m205[0m[39m:            return this;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m206[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m208[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m209[0m[39m:         * Sets whether to use InfoZIP Unicode Extra Fields [0m[1;39m([0m[39mif present[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to set[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe file names.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m210[0m[39m:         *[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m211[0m[39m:         * @param useUnicodeExtraFields whether to use InfoZIP Unicode Extra [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFields [0m[1;39m([0m[39mif present[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to set the file names.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m212[0m[39m:         * @return [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@code this[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m instance.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m213[0m[39m:         *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m214[0m[39m:        public Builder [0m[1;35msetUseUnicodeExtraFields[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal boolean [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39museUnicodeExtraFields[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m215[0m[39m:            this.useUnicodeExtraFields = useUnicodeExtraFields;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m216[0m[39m:            return this;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m217[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/main/java/org/apache/commons/compress/archivers/zip/ZipFile.jav[0m[1;92ma:1550[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1559[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1550[0m[39m:        String commentString = [0m[1;35mentryEncoding.decode[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcomment[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1551[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"https"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1552[0m[39m:            try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream is = new [0m[1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1553[0m[39m:                ByteArrayOutputStream bos = new [0m[1;35mByteArrayOutputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1554[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mIOUtils.copy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mis, bos[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1555[0m[39m:                commentString = new [0m[1;35mString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbos.toByteArray[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mStandardCharsets.UTF_8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1556[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1557[0m[39m:                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95mswallow[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1558[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1559[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview and Root Cause  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The vulnerability arises in `ZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry`: untrusted [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive comments that begin with “http” or “https” are passed directly to `new [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, causing SSRF when a malicious ZIP comment points [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat an external host. The critical logic that must be preserved is ZIP comment [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdecoding and local comment handling; only the conditional remote‐fetch path is [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproblematic.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Proposed Mitigation: Opt-in Remote Comment Fetch  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Introduce a new boolean flag `allowRemoteCommentFetch` in `ZipFile` [0m[1;39m([0m[39msafe [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefault: false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and expose it via the `ZipFile.Builder` API so users can explicitly[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menable remote comment retrieval if desired. Guard the existing URL-fetch block with[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis flag. This eliminates SSRF by default without removing the feature entirely.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Patch Steps  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Add Field to ZipFile  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `ZipFile` class, declare:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       private final boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Initialize it in the main constructor.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Modify Constructors  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Locate the private core constructor:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel,[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               String channelDescription,[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               Charset encoding,[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               boolean useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               boolean closeOnError,[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               boolean ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Expand its signature to add a final parameter `boolean [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowRemoteCommentFetch`.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inside the constructor body, assign `this.allowRemoteCommentFetch = [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowRemoteCommentFetch;`.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Update all callers:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Three deprecated public constructors [0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath-, SeekableByteChannel-based[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould now invoke the extended constructor, passing `false` for [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch` to preserve legacy [0m[1;39m([0m[39msafe[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m behavior.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • In `[0m[1;35mBuilder.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, modify the `new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call to pass the Builder’s[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch` field as the final argument.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Extend Builder API  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `ZipFile.Builder`, add:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       private boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch = false;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       public Builder [0m[1;35msetAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean allow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           this.allowRemoteCommentFetch = allow;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           return this;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `[0m[1;35mBuilder.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, change:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     to:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, ignoreLocalFileHeader, allowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Guard URL Fetch in readCentralDirectoryEntry  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace the unconditional block [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines ~[0m[1;36m1551[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m1558[0m[1;39m)[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"https"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m… [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     with:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallowRemoteCommentFetch[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           && [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"https"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m existing try-openStream logic[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This ensures [0m[1;35mURL.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is never reached when [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[33mallowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[39m==false`.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Functionality  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Local comment decoding and use of central/local header extra fields remain [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muntouched.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Default behavior is now safe: no outbound connections triggered by ZIP [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomments.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing applications that relied on remote comment fetching must explicitly [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall `new [0m[1;35mZipFile.Builder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.setAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Deprecated constructors continue with `[0m[33mallowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[39m=[0m[35mfalse[0m[39m` to avoid[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munexpected network fetches.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects and Mitigations  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Applications expecting remote comment loading will no longer fetch by default;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthey should opt in. Document this behavioral change in release notes.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes to fuzz harness or test code; all existing tests remain valid.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The remote-fetch code path is still available if explicitly enabled, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreserving feature completeness.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Rationale  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A safe-by-default guard eliminates SSRF without removing functionality.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Exposing a Builder flag aligns with existing configuration style [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`setUseUnicodeExtraFields`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introducing a flag and guarding the URL logic is surgical and avoids broad [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchanges or catching of exceptions.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar opt-in patterns exist for other optional ZIP features [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[12/23/25 05:32:31][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=141089;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=996813;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mn evals: [1;36m2[0m, patch status: PatchStatus.UNCOMPILABLE[1m)[0m                                 [2m               [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mZipFile[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile.<init>[0m[1;39m([0m[39mZipFile.jav[0m[1;92ma:971[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile.<init>[0m[1;39m([0m[39mZipFile.jav[0m[1;92ma:938[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile.<init>[0m[1;39m([0m[39mZipFile.jav[0m[1;92ma:876[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35mCompressZipFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCompressZipFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:30[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: b38823cc610751ee[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer-based fuzz test on `org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggered a Server Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m exception when the library attempted[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto fetch ZIP entry comments starting with “http” or “https”. To mitigate untrusted [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremote fetches, a patch was proposed that adds a boolean flag [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m—defaulting to false—and updates constructors and a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuilder method to pass this flag through. After applying the patch, the project [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfails to compile with two type‐mismatch errors in `ZipFile.java`, indicating that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msome constructor call sites were not updated to match the revised method [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignatures.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - During fuzzing, `ZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry` decoded a comment string [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand, if it began with “http”[0m[35m/[0m[39m“https,” opened a remote URL stream.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The Jazzer sanitizer reported `FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium: Server Side Request [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mForgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, noting that untrusted data could be used to exfiltrate data or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprobe internal services.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack trace highlights:  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `ServerSideRequestForgery.checkSsrfSocket` → `java.net.Socket.connect` → [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`HttpURLConnection.getInputStream` → `ZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry` → [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`CompressZipFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introduced a private field `allowRemoteCommentFetch` in `ZipFile`.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Updated the builder [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ZipFile.Builder`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to include [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35msetAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Extended the main `ZipFile` constructor signature to accept [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch`, and passed the flag from builder and deprecated [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructors.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Wrapped the conditional remote fetch in `readCentralDirectoryEntry`: only open[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe URL when `allowRemoteCommentFetch` is true.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Key hunks:  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m New field[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   private final boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   …[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Builder[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   private boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch = false;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   public Builder [0m[1;35msetAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean allow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   …[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Main constructor[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   private [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel, String desc, Charset enc,[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   boolean useUnicodeExtraFields, boolean closeOnError,[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   boolean ignoreLocalFileHeader, boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       this.allowRemoteCommentFetch = allowRemoteCommentFetch;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       …[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   …[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m In [0m[1;35mreadCentralDirectoryEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallowRemoteCommentFetch && [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m …[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream is = new [0m[1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Build Output After Patch  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Maven compilation fails with two errors in `ZipFile.java`:  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     incompatible types: java.lang.String cannot be converted to [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjava.nio.charset.Charset[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     incompatible types: java.nio.charset.Charset cannot be converted to [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjava.lang.String[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - These errors occur at lines where deprecated constructors call the revised [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipFile` constructor with parameters in the wrong order or of the wrong type. For [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexample:  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath path, String encoding, boolean useUnicodeExtraFields, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboolean ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -    throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -    [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mnewReadByteChannel[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -         [0m[1;35mpath.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -         encoding,[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -         useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -         true,[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -         ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -         false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[32m'encoding'[0m[39m is a String, but constructor now expects Charset in this [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mposition[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify all constructor overloads and deprecated entry points into `ZipFile`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensuring parameter lists match the new signature [0m[1;39m([0m[39mseekable channel, description, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCharset vs. String, flags, boolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm the correct conversion between `String` encodings and `Charset` [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstances—update calls of `[0m[1;35mCharset.forName[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or `[0m[1;35mCharset.defaultCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` as [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mneeded.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Examine other factory or convenience methods in `ZipFile` that may still rely [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon the old constructor signatures or pass parameters in the wrong order.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review the builder’s use cases in tests or examples to ensure [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`setAllowRemoteCommentFetch` is propagated correctly.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
