[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview and Root Cause  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The compilation errors stem from the fact that the main private constructor of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipFile` was extended to take a `Charset` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnot a `String`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and an extra `boolean [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowRemoteCommentFetch` flag. However, the three deprecated public constructors [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstill invoke the old signature, passing a `String` where a `Charset` is now [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpected, and they have not supplied the new boolean flag at the end. We must [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdate each of these constructor call sites to [0m[1;39m([0m[39ma[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m convert the `String` encoding to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma `Charset`, and [0m[1;39m([0m[39mb[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m append `false` for `allowRemoteCommentFetch`.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Critical Logic to Preserve  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The semantics of the deprecated constructors must remain unchanged except for [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe new flag default.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The default behavior for `allowRemoteCommentFetch` is `false`.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing flags for `useUnicodeExtraFields`, `closeOnError`, and [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ignoreLocalFileHeader` should be preserved as they were.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The builder path, which already has been updated to propagate the new flag, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmust remain intact.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Step-by‐Step Patch Plan  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. In `ZipFile.java`, locate the three deprecated public constructors [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlines [0m[1;36m859[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m894[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   @Deprecated[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath path, String encoding, boolean useUnicodeExtraFields, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboolean ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   @Deprecated[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   @Deprecated[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel, String encoding[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. For each constructor, rewrite the `[0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call to match the new private [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructor signature:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   i.  Path‐based constructor [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpreserve `closeOnError = true`, pass through [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ignoreLocalFileHeader`, and default `allowRemoteCommentFetch = false`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```java[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       @Deprecated[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath path,[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                      String encoding,[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                      boolean useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                      boolean ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mnewReadByteChannel[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[1;35mpath.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m convert String→Charset[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[1;35mCharsets.toCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mencoding, Builder.DEFAULT_CHARSET[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[39m* closeOnError = *[0m[35m/[0m[39m true,[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[39m* ignoreLocalFileHeader = *[0m[35m/[0m[39m ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[39m* allowRemoteCommentFetch = *[0m[35m/[0m[39m false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ii. SeekableByteChannel no‐encoding constructor [0m[1;39m([0m[39muse the default charset, and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefault both `closeOnError` and `ignoreLocalFileHeader` to their old defaults, then[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch = false`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```java[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       @Deprecated[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchannel,[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[32m"a SeekableByteChannel"[0m[39m,[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m use Builder’s DEFAULT_CHARSET[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                Builder.DEFAULT_CHARSET,[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[39m* useUnicodeExtraFields = *[0m[35m/[0m[39m true,[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[39m* closeOnError = *[0m[35m/[0m[39m false,[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[39m* ignoreLocalFileHeader = *[0m[35m/[0m[39m false,[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[39m* allowRemoteCommentFetch = *[0m[35m/[0m[39m false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   iii. SeekableByteChannel + String‐encoding constructor [0m[1;39m([0m[39mconvert `String` to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Charset`, default other flags, `allowRemoteCommentFetch = false`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```java[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       @Deprecated[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel,[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                      String encoding[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchannel,[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[32m"a SeekableByteChannel"[0m[39m,[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[1;35mCharsets.toCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mencoding, Builder.DEFAULT_CHARSET[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[39m* useUnicodeExtraFields = *[0m[35m/[0m[39m true,[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[39m* closeOnError = *[0m[35m/[0m[39m false,[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[39m* ignoreLocalFileHeader = *[0m[35m/[0m[39m false,[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[35m/[0m[39m* allowRemoteCommentFetch = *[0m[35m/[0m[39m false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Imports and Utilities  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure the utility class `Charsets` is imported:  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `import org.apache.commons.compress.utils.Charsets;`  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Refer to the builder’s default charset via `Builder.DEFAULT_CHARSET`.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Verify the Builder Path  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `[0m[1;35mBuilder.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method has already been updated to call:  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mactualChannel,[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 actualDescription,[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[1;35mgetCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 closeOnError,[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 allowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No further changes are needed there.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Why This Approach Is Optimal  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It directly addresses the compiler errors by matching the revised constructor [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignature.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It preserves existing default behaviors [0m[1;39m([0m[39mencoding, flags[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and simply wires in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe new `allowRemoteCommentFetch` boolean with its intended default of `false`.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It does not touch any harness or fuzzing code, nor external dependencies.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It keeps the public API backward‐compatible [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdeprecated constructors still [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and ensures that users who don’t opt into `allowRemoteCommentFetch` get [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe safe default.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Side Effects and Mitigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Deprecated constructors now convert `String` encodings to `Charset` using the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame `Charsets.toCharset` logic as the main constructor, ensuring consistent [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Defaulting `allowRemoteCommentFetch` to `false` in all entry points maintains [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe security fix’s intent.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other functionality is impacted; all existing tests and fuzzer entry points[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremain valid.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Post‐Patch Verification  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Recompile the entire module to confirm no type‐mismatch errors remain.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re‐run unit tests to verify backward‐compatibility and unchanged behavior of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe deprecated constructors.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Execute the Jazzer fuzz harness to ensure that remote comment fetch is still [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdisabled by default and only enabled when explicitly set via the builder.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe Commons-Compress fuzzers triggered a Jazzer security finding for Server Side [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRequest Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when processing ZIP file comments that begin with “http…” or[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“https…”. An attempted patch introduced a new boolean flag [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mallowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to disable remote fetch of comments by default, added [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorresponding builder methods, and propagated the flag through new and deprecated [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipFile` constructors. The project compiled initially, but after applying the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch the Maven build fails with a compilation error: an incompatible type [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconversion where a `Charset` is passed to a constructor overload expecting a [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`String`.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The Jazzer fuzzing harness for `CompressZipFuzzer` crashed with  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium: Server Side [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRequest Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack trace shows the SSFR check in [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ServerSideRequestForgery.checkSsrfSocket` triggered when the `ZipFile` code [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempts to open a remote URL derived from a ZIP comment [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`new [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in `ZipFile.populateFromCentralDirectory`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This indicates that comments in the archive starting with “http” or “https” [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare automatically fetched, permitting outbound network requests based on untrusted [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marchive data.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A private field `allowRemoteCommentFetch` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault `false`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was added to [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipFile`.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A new builder method `[0m[1;35mBuilder.setAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` was [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprovided.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing constructors [0m[1;39m([0m[39mincluding deprecated ones[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m were modified to accept [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe new boolean flag, propagating it to the main `[0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` constructor. [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDeprecated overloads were updated to pass `false` for the new flag.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the code path that reads entry comments, the condition guarding remote [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfetch was changed from  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"https"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     to  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallowRemoteCommentFetch && [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"https"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Result & Build Log  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The build starts as usual, Maven recompiles `ZipFile.java` and then reports:  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/src/commons-compress/src/main/java/org/apache/commons/compress/archivers/zip/[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [95mZipFile.java[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m984[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m61[0m[1;39m][0m[39m [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       incompatible types: java.nio.charset.Charset cannot be converted to [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjava.lang.String[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The error refers to a constructor call at line [0m[1;36m984[0m[39m where the patch replaced a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`String` argument with a `Charset` instance, but the deprecated constructor [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignature still expects a `String`.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Code Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Constructor Overloads in ZipFile.java**  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Verify all `[0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` constructors’ signatures and ensure that the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msequence and types of arguments match across builder, new, and deprecated entry [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoints.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Builder vs. Deprecated Constructors**  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Check that `[0m[1;35mBuilder.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and all deprecated constructors consistently invoke[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe same canonical constructor signature. Any mismatch in argument order or type [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g., `String` vs. `Charset`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will cause compilation failures.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Charset Handling Utilities**  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Inspect calls to `[0m[1;35mCharsets.toCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Builder.DEFAULT_CHARSET_NAME`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`DEFAULT_CHARSET` to confirm correct usage when [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconverting between `String` and `Charset`.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **populateFromCentralDirectory and Comment Fetch**  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Review the code in `[0m[1;35mpopulateFromCentralDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` where comments are decoded[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand potentially fetched. Ensure the new flag is checked in all relevant paths and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat no other remote-fetch code remains unguarded.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m864[0m[39m:     * Opens the given channel for reading, assuming [0m[32m"UTF-8"[0m[39m for file names.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m865[0m[39m:     * <p>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m866[0m[39m:     * [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link org.apache.commons.compress.utils.SeekableInMemoryByteChannel[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallows you to read from an in-memory archive.[0m                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m984[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m985[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m986[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m987[0m[39m:     * Opens the given file for reading, assuming the specified encoding for [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfile names, scanning unicode extra fields.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m988[0m[39m:     *[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/main/java/org/apache/commons/compress/archivers/zip/ZipFile.jav[0m[1;92ma:820[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m824[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m820[0m[39m:    public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal Path path, final String encoding[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m821[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath, encoding, true[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/main/java/org/apache/commons/compress/archivers/zip/ZipFile.jav[0m[1;92ma:981[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m988[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m981[0m[39m:    @Deprecated[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m982[0m[39m:    public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal String name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m983[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnew [0m[1;35mFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, DEFAULT_CHARSET_NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m984[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m985[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m986[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m987[0m[39m:     * Opens the given file for reading, assuming the specified encoding for [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfile names, scanning unicode extra fields.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m988[0m[39m:     *[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The compilation failure arises because the patch altered the chain of `ZipFile` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructors—adding a new `allowRemoteCommentFetch` flag and converting some [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`String`‐based encoding parameters to `Charset`—but did not uniformly update all [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpublic/deprecated overloads.  In particular, the deprecated `[0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the two‐ and three‐argument `[0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath, String…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` overloads still forward to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructors expecting a `String` or the old number of parameters, leading to a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Charset → String` mismatch.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Canonical “target” constructor  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Retain a single private “kernel” constructor signature that all public overloads[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdelegate to:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     private [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel,[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     String                 channelDescription,[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     Charset                encoding,[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     boolean                useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     boolean                closeOnError,[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     boolean                ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     boolean                allowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     throws IOException[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Update public/deprecated constructors  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   For each public or deprecated overload, _do not_ change its signature.  Instead,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrevise its body so that it always calls the canonical constructor above, converting[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many `String encoding` to `Charset` via `[0m[1;35mCharsets.toCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or using [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Builder.DEFAULT_CHARSET`, and supplying default values for the two new booleans [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`closeOnError` and `ignoreLocalFileHeader`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m as per the original semantics, plus [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch = false`.  Concretely:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Old body: `[0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnew [0m[1;35mFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, DEFAULT_CHARSET_NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - **New body**:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mnewReadByteChannel[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnew [0m[1;35mFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            new [0m[1;35mFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            Builder.DEFAULT_CHARSET,[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*useUnicodeExtraFields*[0m[35m/[0m[39m true,[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*closeOnError*[0m[35m/[0m[39m true,[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*ignoreLocalFileHeader*[0m[35m/[0m[39m false,[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*allowRemoteCommentFetch*[0m[35m/[0m[39m false[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      This ensures no `String` is passed to a `String`‐only overload, and matches [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe canonical constructor directly.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath path, String encoding[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Old body: `[0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath, encoding, true[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - **New body**:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mnewReadByteChannel[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mpath.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mCharsets.toCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mencoding, Builder.DEFAULT_CHARSET[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*useUnicodeExtraFields*[0m[35m/[0m[39m true,[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*closeOnError*[0m[35m/[0m[39m true,[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*ignoreLocalFileHeader*[0m[35m/[0m[39m false,[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*allowRemoteCommentFetch*[0m[35m/[0m[39m false[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath path, String encoding, boolean useUnicodeExtraFields[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Old body: `[0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath, encoding, useUnicodeExtraFields, false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - **New body**:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mnewReadByteChannel[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mpath.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mCharsets.toCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mencoding, Builder.DEFAULT_CHARSET[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*closeOnError*[0m[35m/[0m[39m true,[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*ignoreLocalFileHeader*[0m[35m/[0m[39m false,[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*allowRemoteCommentFetch*[0m[35m/[0m[39m false[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. @Deprecated public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath path, String encoding, boolean [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39museUnicodeExtraFields, boolean ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Already patched to call the canonical constructor with [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCharsets.toCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `false` for `allowRemoteCommentFetch`.  **Verify** [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe two flags `closeOnError` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mshould be `true`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and `ignoreLocalFileHeader` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpassed argument[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m align with original defaults.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. @Deprecated public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Update similarly if not already done:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            channel,[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[32m"a SeekableByteChannel"[0m[39m,[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            Builder.DEFAULT_CHARSET,[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*useUnicodeExtraFields*[0m[35m/[0m[39m true,[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*closeOnError*[0m[35m/[0m[39m false,          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m or true if original behavior was to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclose on error[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*ignoreLocalFileHeader*[0m[35m/[0m[39m false,[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*allowRemoteCommentFetch*[0m[35m/[0m[39m false[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   f. @Deprecated public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel, String encoding[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - New body:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            channel,[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[32m"a SeekableByteChannel"[0m[39m,[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mCharsets.toCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mencoding, Builder.DEFAULT_CHARSET[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*useUnicodeExtraFields*[0m[35m/[0m[39m true,[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*closeOnError*[0m[35m/[0m[39m false,[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*ignoreLocalFileHeader*[0m[35m/[0m[39m false,[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[39m*allowRemoteCommentFetch*[0m[35m/[0m[39m false[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Why this works  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Type correctness**: All calls to the canonical constructor supply a [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Charset` where expected—no stray `String → Charset` or `Charset → String` [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatches remain.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Preserved API**: Public/deprecated constructor signatures are unchanged, so [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting clients, tests, and fuzzing harnesses compile and work exactly as before, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith network fetch disabled by default.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Single code path**: Every overload funnels into one place—the private [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructor—making future maintenance [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., adjusting defaults[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m straightforward.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **No harness or utility change**: We only touch `ZipFile.java`, leave fuzzing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness, tests, and external libraries untouched.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential side effects and mitigation  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **closeOnError default**: Verify that `closeOnError` defaults [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`true` for [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfile‐based, `false` for channel‐based[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m match the original behavior.  Adjust if [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtests rely on the previous setting.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **ignoreLocalFileHeader default**: The default [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`false`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m should be the same as[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore; confirm against original code.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Deprecation notices**: These constructors are already deprecated in favor of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Builder`; updating internals will not affect deprecation warnings.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Null‐encoding handling**: `[0m[1;35mCharsets.toCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnull, [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBuilder.DEFAULT_CHARSET[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` will yield the UTF‐[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m default, preserving original “null =[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mplatform default” behavior [0m[1;39m([0m[39mas per existing code[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Verification  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re‐run `mvn compile` to confirm no more `incompatible types` errors.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rerun the fuzzers to ensure SSRF fetch is disabled by default but can be [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menabled via the builder.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Execute the existing test suite to validate no regressions in ZIP file parsing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor encoding handling.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure code coverage and behavior around `[0m[1;35mpopulateFromCentralDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremains unchanged except for the new `allowRemoteCommentFetch` guard.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis comprehensive normalization of constructor delegation will resolve the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation error and maintain existing functionality.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn SSRF [0m[1;39m([0m[39mServer-Side Request Forgery[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m issue was detected when the Apache Commons [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCompress `ZipFile` implementation fetched ZIP entry comments beginning with “http” [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor “https” via `new [0m[1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. A patch was proposed to introduce a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboolean flag [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m—defaulting to false—to disable automatic [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremote comment fetching unless explicitly enabled. The patch added this flag to the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipFile` class, its builder, and all deprecated constructors, and wrapped the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mURL‐fetch logic in a conditional check. When building the code after applying the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch, the compilation failed with three errors:  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. “call to this must be first statement in constructor”  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. “incompatible types: java.nio.charset.Charset cannot be converted to [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjava.lang.String”  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. A second “call to this must be first statement in constructor”  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A Jazzer‐based fuzz test [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`CompressZipFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggered a security sanitizer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`ServerSideRequestForgery.checkSsrf`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the JAZZER API, indicating an SSRF risk. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace shows that during ZIP processing [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`ZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry` and `populateFromCentralDirectory`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, a comment[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstring beginning with “http” or “https” caused `[0m[1;35mURL.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to be invoked, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleading to an attempted outbound connection [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`jazze.com:[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The sanitizer flagged this as a medium‐severity security issue: untrusted comment[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata resulting in external requests.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A new private final field `allowRemoteCommentFetch` was added to `ZipFile`.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `ZipFile.Builder` was extended with `[0m[1;35msetAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The primary `ZipFile` constructor signature was extended to accept the new flag, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand all existing constructors [0m[1;39m([0m[39mincluding deprecated overloads that take `Path`, [0m    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m74[0m[39m: * Replacement for [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link java.util.zip.ZipFile[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m75[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m76[0m[39m: * This class adds support for file name encodings other than UTF-[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrequired to work on ZIP files created by native ZIP tools and is able to skip a[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m77[0m[39m: * preamble like the one found in self extracting archives. Furthermore it [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturns instances of[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m78[0m[39m: * [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@code org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipArchiveEntry[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m instead of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m[39m@link java.util.zip.ZipEntry[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mp[0m[39m>[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m80[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m: * It doesn't extend [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link java.util.zip.ZipFile[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m as it would have to [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreimplement all methods anyway. Like [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link java.util.zip.ZipFile[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m, it uses[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m: * SeekableByteChannel under the covers and supports compressed and uncompressed[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentries. As of Apache Commons Compress [0m[1;36m1.3[0m[39m it also transparently supports Zip64[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m83[0m[39m: * extensions and thus individual entries and archives larger than [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m GB or with [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmore than [0m[1;36m65[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m536[0m[39m entries.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mp[0m[39m>[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m: * The method signatures mimic the ones of [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link java.util.zip.ZipFile[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m, with a[0m [2m                [0m
